SyncChartAreas Demo
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>Essential Chart for WPF enables a user to add any number of chart areas with single primary axis and can customize the size of the chart area using the Splitter</Paragraph><Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="images/SyncChartAreas Demo.png" Width="750" Height="520" /></Paragraph>

<Paragraph  FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16" TextAlignment="Center">
Fig: <Bold> SyncChartAreas Demo</Bold>
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Every area inside the SyncChartAreas shares the same primary axis.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Each area can be populated with any number of secondary axes.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>SplitterVisibility to set the visibility for the Splitter</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>SplitterWidth to set Width for the Splitter</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>SplitterColor to set the Interior  for the Splitter</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>SplitterStroke to set the stroke color for the Splitter</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Splitter visibility"</Bold> sets the visibility of the splitter. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The text box <Bold>"Splitter width"</Bold> sets the width of the splitter. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Splitter color"</Bold> sets the color for the splitter. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Splitter stroke"</Bold> sets the color for the Splitter stroke </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The slider <Bold>"Splitter position"</Bold> sets the position of the splitter </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

</List>


</FlowDocument>